reviewText: The DVD starts out with Dr. Shock in what looks like a typical local horror host set up and he gives someone a hair cut and introduces the 3, half hour movies. None of the 3 are very good, all feature bad acting, okay effects (some okay, some downright terrible), lame jokes and no skin (not counting the Frankenstein looking breasts in the vampire segment.) I wish it was a little more original (you can see where all of the stories are going well in advance.)
This was not the one that didn't work! I'm sorry. This movie set is ok. It has three films on it and I rate it ok.
